  "response": "Whether 25 is the right age to get married depends on many personal factors, such as:\n\n1. Individual maturity\n2. Emotional readiness\n3. Financial stability\n4. Relationship quality\n5. Personal goals and career plans\n6. Cultural and family expectations\n\nThere's no universal \"right\" age to marry. Some people marry successfully in their early 20s, while others wait until their 30s or later. What matters most is:\n\n- You both feel committed and ready\n- You communicate well\n- You share similar life goals\n- You are financially and emotionally prepared for marriage\n\nIf you're unsure, it might help to:\n- Discuss long-term plans together\n- Ensure you're both on the same page\n- Consider premarital counseling\n- Take time to know each other deeply\n\nUltimately, the decision is personal and should be based on your unique circumstances and relationship.",
